IX. HORATIUS COCLES.

Horatius cocles: note that his surname, like many of the Roman cegrnemina, was derived from a personal peculiarity. The story of Horatius was one of the most celebrated legends of the early history of Rome, and has been made one of the most familiar to modern readers by Macaulay⁵s Lay of Horatius. Our version is a combination of the two.
